race.comment: TINO BANNER (8) shapes well for this after finishing third last start over 324m at Richmond Straight but in a scintillating 17.33 behind Cawbourne Leota. Rates a top chance if runs up to latest. SLICK RAZOR (1) was a last start winner (22.57) at this track who is building a strong winning record. Comes through a solid form race last start. In great recent form and expected to measure up again. MAKO BEAST (7) has been a little hard to follow, finishing out of the placings latest but was in winning form two back scoring in a Maiden at Richmond Straight. Expecting sharp improvement this line-up. JUST LIKE MIA (4) should be thereabouts despite an unplaced run here most recently.
